      <p>Kitulgala, a small jungle town about 90 minutes east of Colombo on the Kelani River, is Sri Lanka's white-water rafting capital. The Kelani River runs fast and clear through dense rainforest here, producing a series of Grade 2–4 rapids over a 4–5km stretch that makes for an exhilarating half-day adventure. Kitulgala is best known internationally as the filming location for David Lean's 1957 film The Bridge on the River Kwai — the bridge itself was built here and then destroyed for the film's climax. Today the setting is equally dramatic, with lush jungle canopy, abundant birdlife, and the rush of the river making Kitulgala one of Sri Lanka's most enjoyable day trips.</p>

      <h2>The Rapids</h2>
      <p>The Kelani River at Kitulgala offers roughly 8–10 named rapids over the standard rafting section, ranging from Grade 2 (straightforward for beginners) to Grade 4 (requiring teamwork and paddling technique). Highlights include <strong>Killer Falls</strong> (Grade 3+, the most dramatic drop on the route), <strong>Temple Rock</strong> (Grade 3), and several continuous Grade 2 sections where the river broadens over smooth boulders. Between rapids the river calms to allow swimming — jumping from boulders into deep jade pools is as much a part of the Kitulgala experience as the rafting itself. The total water time is typically 2–3 hours.</p>

      <h2>What to Expect</h2>
      <p>All operators provide safety helmets, life jackets and paddles. A safety briefing covers paddle commands, falling-from-the-raft positions (feet up, facing downstream), and how to re-enter the raft. Guides lead from the front of each raft — their experience and route knowledge is critical at the Grade 3–4 sections. Groups of 4–8 people per raft. No experience is necessary for the standard route; reasonable swimming ability and comfort in water is assumed. The minimum age is typically 12. Non-swimmers can participate with a guide's approval and a more conservative seat position in the raft.</p>

      <AffiliateBox title="Book a Kitulgala Rafting Day Trip" description="Most operators run full-day packages from Colombo including transport, rafting, a riverside lunch and optional cliff jumping." buttonText="Book Rafting Tour" buttonHref="https://www.getyourguide.com/sri-lanka-l976/" variant="tour" />

      <h2>Operators and Pricing</h2>
      <p>Multiple operators are based in Kitulgala, ranging from well-established adventure companies to smaller local outfits. Pricing for the standard rafting session runs approximately USD 25–45 per person depending on group size and whether transport from Colombo is included. Full-day packages from Colombo (including pickup, rafting, riverside lunch and optional cliff jumping or canyoning) run USD 60–90 per person. Book through reputable adventure operators rather than unnamed touts. Key operators include Borderlands, Adventure Lanka and Adrenaline Rush — all maintain equipment to international safety standards.</p>

      <h2>Best Time to Go</h2>
      <p>The Kelani River runs year-round but water levels vary considerably with the seasons. The best rafting is typically during or just after the wet season — <strong>October to January</strong> for the highest water levels and most powerful rapids. The dry season (February–April) brings lower water but clearer visibility and warmer swimming pools between rapids. Rafting is suspended during extreme flood conditions — operators will advise. Kitulgala is in Sri Lanka's wet zone and receives rain year-round, so pack accordingly.</p>

      <h2>Combining with Other Activities</h2>
      <p>Kitulgala also offers canyoning, abseiling, rock climbing, camping, and bird watching (the surrounding Kelani Valley Forest Reserve is one of the best sites for wet zone endemic birds, including the elusive Serendib scops owl). It makes a good overnight stop between Colombo and Kandy on the highland circuit — the journey through the rubber and spice plantations east of Colombo is itself scenic. Stay at one of several riverside guesthouses for a longer adventure camping experience.</p>
